//                   Wrapper classes
// as a solution to this problem ,Java allows you to include the primitives in the family of objects by using what are called wrapper classes.
// there is a wrapper class for every primitive  data type in java.
// this class encapulate a single value for the primitive data type.
// for instance the class for int is Integer , for float is Float and so on.


//    Primitive type                      Wrapper class
//    boolen        ----------------------Boolen
//    byte          ----------------------Byte
//    char          ----------------------Char
//    short         ----------------------Short
//    int           ----------------------Int





// use of import keyword in java
// import is a keyword in java
// its used to import classes of the other packages.
